Key Match Events: Gerrit Cole struck out nine over six innings before exiting due to a cramp
Giancarlo Stanton homered to reach 25 homers for the 10th time in his career
Aaron Judge doubled for his MLB-best 124th RBI
Gleyber Torres had three hits, including a two-run double in the third inning
Anthony Rizzo had a two-run double in the fifth inning
Anthony Volpe and Alex Verdugo had one-out singles in the third inning
Marcus Semien's grounder was stopped by Gleyber Torres for an out in the ninth inning
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Judge expressed pride in the team's resilience after the comeback win
Gerrit Cole will be managing his cramp situation moving forward
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was part of a series between the two teams
Luke Weaver took over for Gerrit Cole after he left the game with a cramp
Clarke Schmidt struck out seven without a walk in a rehab start for Double-A Somerset
Austin Wells stayed in the game after getting hit on a hand by a pitch
Luis Gil is expected to rejoin the rotation this week
